All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Application
The Application class is the entry point of the Wallet Service application.
Audit
The Audit class is responsible for logging audit information to a file.
InsufficientFundsException
The InsufficientFundsException class represents an exception that is thrown when there are insufficient funds to perform a certain operation.
Main
The Main class serves as the entry point for the application.
MenuInput
The MenuInput class handles user input for menu actions.
MenuOutput
The MenuOutput class handles printing menu options and messages.
NotUniqueTransactionIdException
The NotUniqueTransactionIdException class represents an exception that is thrown when a transaction ID is not unique.
Player
A class representing a player in the system.
PlayerAlreadyExistsException
The PlayerAlreadyExistsException class represents an exception that is thrown when attempting to create a player that already exists.
PlayerInput
The PlayerInput class handles user input related to player authentication.
PlayerNotFoundException
The PlayerNotFoundException class represents an exception that is thrown when a player could not be found.
PlayerOutput
The PlayerOutput class handles displaying player account information.
PlayerRepository
The PlayerRepository interface represents a data access object for managing Player objects.
PlayerRepositoryImpl
The PlayerRepositoryImpl class represents a data access object for managing Player objects.
PlayerService
The PlayerService class handles the business logic operations related to players.
PlayerServiceTest
The PlayerServiceTest class is responsible for testing the methods in the PlayerService class.
Transaction
A class representing a transaction in the system.
Transaction.Type
Enum representing the two types of transactions: debit and credit.
TransactionInput
The TransactionInput class handles user input related to transactions.
TransactionOutput
The TransactionOutput class handles displaying transaction history to the output console.
TransactionRepository
The TransactionRepository interface represents a data access object for managing Transaction objects.
TransactionRepositoryImpl
The TransactionRepositoryImpl class represents a data access object for managing Transaction objects.
TransactionService
The TransactionService class provides methods for crediting, debiting, and retrieving transactions for a player.
TransactionServiceTest
This class contains unit tests for the TransactionService class.
UnknownTransactionException
The UnknownTransactionException class represents an exception that is thrown when an unknown or invalid transaction occurs.
